---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = "How It Works — Is My NBN Cooked?";
const description = "Learn how the Rort Scale rating works, how we calculate effective pricing, and where the plan data comes from.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/how-it-works">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-10">
      <a href="/" class="text-sm text-neutral-500 hover:text-accent transition-colors">&larr; Back to plan checker</a>
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl sm:text-4xl mb-3">How it works</h1>
    <p class="text-neutral-400 mb-12">
      Everything you need to know about how we compare NBN plans and calculate your rort rating.
    </p>

    <!-- The Rort Scale -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl mb-4">The Rort Scale</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-6">
        After you enter your monthly price, we compare it against the cheapest available plan at the same
        speed tier and assign you a rating. Here's what each level means:
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-surface-raised border border-surface-border rounded-xl px-5 py-4">
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full mt-1 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #22d3ee;"></div>
          <div>
            <div class="font-bold" style="color: #22d3ee;">Winning</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mt-0.5">You're paying <span class="text-neutral-300">less</span> than the cheapest plan we track. Whatever you did, don't change a thing.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-surface-raised border border-surface-border rounded-xl px-5 py-4">
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full mt-1 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #4ade80;"></div>
          <div>
            <div class="font-bold" style="color: #4ade80;">Sweet As</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mt-0.5">0–4% above the cheapest available plan. You're on a fair deal — no need to churn.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-surface-raised border border-surface-border rounded-xl px-5 py-4">
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full mt-1 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #facc15;"></div>
          <div>
            <div class="font-bold" style="color: #facc15;">Bit Shit</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mt-0.5">5–14% above the cheapest available plan. Not the end of the world, but money's money — worth having a look around.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-surface-raised border border-surface-border rounded-xl px-5 py-4">
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full mt-1 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #fb923c;"></div>
          <div>
            <div class="font-bold" style="color: #fb923c;">Taking the Piss</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mt-0.5">15–29% above the cheapest available plan. Your provider is having a laugh. Seriously consider churning.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 bg-surface-raised border border-surface-border rounded-xl px-5 py-4">
          <div class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full mt-1 flex-shrink-0" style="background-color: #ef4444;"></div>
          <div>
            <div class="font-bold" style="color: #ef4444;">Absolute Rort</div>
            <div class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mt-0.5">30%+ above the cheapest available plan. Mate. You're getting absolutely done. Switch immediately.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Effective pricing -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl mb-4">How effective pricing works</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-4">
        Many ISPs advertise a low introductory price that reverts to a higher rate after a promo period,
        and some plans charge a one-off setup fee. Comparing the headline price alone is misleading.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-4">
        To produce a fair comparison we calculate the <span class="text-neutral-300 font-medium">effective monthly cost</span>
        — the true average you'll pay over the commitment period:
      </p>
      <div class="bg-surface-raised border border-surface-border rounded-xl px-5 py-4 font-mono text-sm text-neutral-300 mb-4">
        effective cost = (promo months × promo price + remaining months × full price + setup fee) ÷ commitment period
      </div>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
        This means a plan with a great intro offer but a steep post-promo price may rank lower than one with
        a flat rate that's genuinely cheap — which is exactly what you want to know before signing up.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Commitment period selector -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl mb-4">The commitment period selector</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-4">
        The commitment period selector (shown on each speed-tier page) lets you choose how many months you
        plan to stay with your next provider: 3, 6, 12, or 24 months. Changing it recalculates every
        plan's effective cost and re-ranks the table accordingly.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-4">
        The <span class="text-neutral-300 font-medium">Auto: cheapest</span> default picks the horizon
        that produces the single lowest effective monthly cost across all plans. When two horizons tie, it
        leans toward the longer one — which sounds sensible, but read on.
      </p>

      <!-- Churn tip callout -->
      <div class="bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/30 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 mb-4">
        <div class="font-medium text-amber-400 mb-1">The churn trick most people miss</div>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
          Most NBN plans are <span class="text-neutral-300 font-medium">no lock-in</span> — you can
          leave whenever you like. That means a 12-month horizon only makes sense if you're actually
          planning to sit still for a year. If you're willing to churn every 6 months, set the selector
          to <span class="text-neutral-300">6 months</span> and pick the cheapest plan at that horizon.
          Ride out the promo, then switch again. Repeat. You'll consistently beat the plan that "Auto:
          cheapest" picks over 12 months.
        </p>
        <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mt-2">
          <span class="text-amber-400 font-medium">Catch:</span> always check the notice period before
          you churn. Some providers require 30 days' notice — so "month-to-month" doesn't always mean
          you can leave tomorrow. The notice period is listed in each plan's detail row on the comparison
          table, and you can filter to only show plans with no notice required.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
        Short-term: favour plans with long promo periods and no setup fee. Long-term: favour plans with
        low ongoing rates. The selector makes that trade-off obvious at a glance.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Data source -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl mb-4">Where the data comes from</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-4">
        All plan data is sourced from <a href="https://www.netbargains.com.au" class="underline hover:text-white transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NetBargains</a>,
        an independent Australian site that tracks NBN and fixed-line internet plans across every provider.
        Prices are refreshed daily.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm mb-4">
        This site has <span class="text-neutral-300 font-medium">no affiliate links, no ads, and no sponsored placements</span>.
        Rankings are based purely on price. If you find this useful and want to support someone,
        consider chucking a few bucks at
        <a href="https://www.netbargains.com.au" class="underline hover:text-white transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NetBargains</a>
        — the legends who actually maintain the plan data.
      </p>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm">
        Prices, availability, and plan details may be out of date, inaccurate, or wrong.
        Always check the provider's website before signing up.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="border-t border-surface-border pt-8 text-center">
      <a href="/" class="inline-block bg-accent hover:bg-accent/90 text-white font-medium rounded-lg px-6 py-3 transition-colors">
        Check your plan now
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
